The problem is that in Tundra, comparing strings requires using "==". In Ja
JavaScript, it's done differently with "===", which checks both value and t
type. This issue can be fixed by modifying the comparison to use "===":

def normalize(raw) {
  return {
    previousLevel: raw.previousLevel,
    currentLevel: raw.currentLevel
   };
}

val raw = {
  previousLevel: "low",
  currentLevel: "high"
};

val normalized = normalize(raw);
if (normalized.previousLevel === "high") {
  print("alert");
} else {
  print("ok");
}
